Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer, Backend* with *CDW*. I bring over three years of professional experience designing and maintaining production-grade backend systems, REST and GraphQL APIs, and cloud-native AWS workloads, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and maintained REST and GraphQL APIs for an MCP AI interaction layer that translates natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and information security controls across a distributed surface. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented a full observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith (tracing, structured logs, evaluation hooks) mirroring New Relic-style monitoring, and optimized concurrent multi-agent orchestration via LangChain and LangGraph to cut end-to-end latency by 60% and AWS API costs by 50%. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis handling file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs — with full unit and integration test coverage. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications, with CI/CD pipelines enforcing quality and security gates on every release, and developed AWS Step Functions workflows to orchestrate long-running data import jobs and prevent Lambda timeouts. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to CDW's core engineering responsibilities — developing and maintaining REST and GraphQL APIs, integrating with services like AWS and New Relic, and upholding test-driven development and security best practices in containerized, Kubernetes-based production environments.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, GPU-accelerated computing, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture CDW values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed the full model development lifecycle from training on Pace's HPC cluster to containerized inference deployment via vLLM and Hugging Face. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming and AI agent development for 50+ students — requiring me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly, directly mirroring the knowledge-sharing and cross-team technical guidance responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to CDW's Product Development team.

I have always been passionate about making technology work so people can do great things, and about fostering teamwork, integrity, and customer focus in everything I build. I envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of CDW's mission to help customers navigate an increasingly complex IT market and maximize return on their technology investments. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

